<concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="topic_7_3_3">
   <title>Tailing Logs Files</title>
   <conbody>
      <p>You can view the log files using any text editor, or you can view the most recent entries
      using the <codeph>tail</codeph> command.</p>
      <p>To view data logged to a file</p>
      <p>
         <codeph>tail -f /opt/hexis/hawkeye-ap/var/log/collector/&lt;<i>logfile</i>&gt;</codeph>
      </p>
      <p>where <codeph>&lt;<i>logfile</i>&gt;</codeph> is <filepath>activity</filepath>,
        <filepath>error</filepath>, or <filepath>transaction</filepath>.</p>
      <p>To view data logged to syslog</p>
      <p>
         <codeph>tail -f /var/log/messages</codeph>
      </p>
   </conbody>
</concept>